---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const basePath = base.endsWith("/") ? base : `${base}/`;
const pathFor = (path = "") => `${basePath}${path.replace(/^\/+/, "")}`;
---
<Base
  title="The Letter"
  description="A personal invitation to Saranagada, Kandhamal: not a tour package, but a slower way to arrive."
  image="photos/01-river-fisherman.jpeg"
>
  <article class="home">
    <section class="home-hero full-bleed" aria-label="The Weight of Belonging">
      <img src={pathFor("photos/01-river-fisherman.jpeg")} alt="Red-soil river, fisherman with bamboo net, Saranagada" />
      <div class="hero-shade"></div>
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">Saranagada · Kandhamal · Odisha</p>
        <h1>The Weight of Belonging</h1>
        <p>
          This is not a tour. There is a village. I would like to host you there,
          slowly, after November 2027.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="primary-link" href="#letter">Read the letter</a>
          <a class="secondary-link" href={pathFor("dispatch")}>Open dispatches</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-coordinates">20.42 N · 84.18 E · Saranagada</div>
    </section>

    <section id="letter" class="letter-intro">
      <div class="intro-copy">
        <p class="section-kicker">Dear stranger</p>
        <p class="lede">
          There is a village in <span class="odia">Kandhamal<span class="odia-tooltip">Kandhamal, Odisha</span></span>
          — red soil, a small river that swells in July, a temple that gathers the street at dusk —
          and there is me, writing to you from Bangalore while I finish my articleship.
        </p>
        <p>
          When that is done, in November of next year, I will be home. If you would like
          to come then, I would like to host you.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="arrival-notes" aria-label="Visit notes">
        <div>
          <span>First guest</span>
          <strong>After Nov 2027</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Stay</span>
          <strong>3 days to a month</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Bring</span>
          <strong>Time, attention, humility</strong>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="identity-grid">
      <div class="identity-copy">
        <p class="section-kicker">Who is writing</p>
        <h2>I left, like most of us do. I am writing because I do not want to lose what I left.</h2>
        <p>
          My name is Chandan. I am a CA finalist. I was born in Saranagada, a village
          of maybe six hundred people, three or four streets, one
          <span class="odia">mandir<span class="odia-tooltip">temple</span></span> that matters,
          and a <span class="odia">haat<span class="odia-tooltip">weekly market</span></span>
          that still runs on Tuesdays.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="portrait-stack">
        <figure class="media-frame tall">
          <img src={pathFor("photos/12-hills-portrait.jpeg")} alt="Hills of Kandhamal" />
        </figure>
        <figure class="media-frame low">
          <img src={pathFor("photos/10-paddy-path.jpeg")} alt="Paddy fields with a thin path" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="plainly full-bleed">
      <div class="plainly-inner">
        <div>
          <p class="section-kicker">The village, plainly</p>
          <h2>There is no performance here. There is work, rain, laughter, worry, and a stranger is fed first.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="plainly-text">
          <p>
            There is a river. There are farmers. The rains come heavy and the work stops
            and the old men sit on a <span class="odia">charpai<span class="odia-tooltip">woven cot</span></span>
            and argue about nothing. There is no reliable internet past the mandir.
          </p>
          <p>
            The school is dying. New English-medium schools have opened in the next town
            and nobody knows who is teaching well and who is just collecting fees.
          </p>
          <p>
            There are boys my age who do not work, who drink
            <span class="odia">handia<span class="odia-tooltip">rice beer</span></span> from afternoon,
            who have lately been moving <span class="odia">ganja<span class="odia-tooltip">cannabis</span></span>
            to the cities. Some have been caught. Some have served jail. Their fathers do not speak of it.
          </p>
          <p>
            And still — the moon is enormous here. The sky is clear. People laugh loudly.
            I am not selling you anything. I am telling you what is there.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="photo-river" aria-label="Photos from Saranagada">
      <figure class="media-frame">
        <img src={pathFor("photos/11-wide-fields.jpeg")} alt="Wide fields of Saranagada" />
      </figure>
      <figure class="media-frame">
        <img src={pathFor("photos/13-temple-collage.jpeg")} alt="Temple at dusk" />
      </figure>
      <figure class="media-frame">
        <img src={pathFor("photos/07-sunset-tree.jpeg")} alt="Sunset from the field" />
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="day-section">
      <div class="day-heading">
        <p class="section-kicker">What a day looks like</p>
        <h2>We will not plan too much.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="day-list">
        <div>
          <span>01</span>
          <h3>Tea before the sun</h3>
          <p>We wake early. The village is already beginning before the light is clean.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>02</span>
          <h3>Walk to the haat</h3>
          <p>If it is Tuesday, the weekly market decides the morning.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>03</span>
          <h3>Mandir at dusk</h3>
          <p>The community gathers, talks, plans the next festival, and stretches the evening.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>04</span>
          <h3>Whatever arrives</h3>
          <p>If there is a wedding we help. If someone's buffalo has calved we go look.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="invitation-panel">
      <div>
        <p class="section-kicker">What I ask of you</p>
        <h2>Come without a camera pointed at poverty.</h2>
        <p>
          Come with a notebook if you write. Come willing to eat what is cooked,
          walk where we walk, sleep in a room that is clean but not designed.
          Stay three days, or ten, or a month. You propose; I respond.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a class="primary-link" href="mailto:chandanpanda615@gmail.com?subject=I%20would%20like%20to%20visit%20Saranagada">Write a letter</a>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
.home {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 88px;
}

.home-hero {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 70svh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-end;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: var(--forest-deep);
}

.home-hero > img {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

.hero-shade {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background:
    linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(16, 38, 31, 0.88), rgba(16, 38, 31, 0.35) 55%, rgba(16, 38, 31, 0.12)),
    linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(16, 38, 31, 0.72), rgba(16, 38, 31, 0.08));
}

.hero-content {
  position: relative;
  width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 40px));
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 96px 0 82px;
  color: var(--paper-soft);
}

.hero-content h1 {
  max-width: 720px;
  margin-bottom: 22px;
  font-size: var(--fs-3xl);
  line-height: 0.96;
  font-weight: 500;
}

.hero-content p:not(.eyebrow) {
  max-width: 560px;
  font-size: var(--fs-lg);
  color: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.88);
}

.hero-actions {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 12px;
  margin-top: 30px;
}

.hero-coordinates {
  position: absolute;
  right: max(20px, calc((100vw - 1180px) / 2));
  bottom: 28px;
  color: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.72);
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: var(--fs-xs);
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.letter-intro {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 330px;
  gap: 56px;
  align-items: start;
}

.intro-copy {
  max-width: 760px;
}

.lede {
  font-size: var(--fs-xl);
  line-height: 1.45;
  color: var(--forest-deep);
}

.arrival-notes {
  display: grid;
  gap: 1px;
  background: var(--line);
  border: 1px solid var(--line);
}

.arrival-notes div {
  padding: 22px;
  background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.76);
}

.arrival-notes span {
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 7px;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: var(--fs-xs);
  color: var(--soil);
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.arrival-notes strong {
  display: block;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--forest);
}

.identity-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(320px, 1fr);
  gap: 56px;
  align-items: center;
}

.identity-copy h2,
.plainly h2,
.day-heading h2,
.invitation-panel h2 {
  font-size: var(--fs-2xl);
  line-height: 1.12;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--forest-deep);
}

.portrait-stack {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 0.86fr 1fr;
  align-items: end;
  gap: 16px;
}

.portrait-stack .tall {
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
}

.portrait-stack .low {
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
  margin-bottom: 42px;
}

.plainly {
  background: var(--forest-deep);
  color: var(--paper-soft);
}

.plainly-inner {
  width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 40px));
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 0.86fr 1fr;
  gap: 64px;
  padding: 88px 0;
}

.plainly h2 {
  color: var(--paper-soft);
}

.plainly .section-kicker {
  color: var(--marigold);
}

.plainly-text {
  color: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.82);
}

.plainly .odia {
  border-bottom-color: var(--marigold);
}

.photo-river {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.8fr 0.9fr;
  gap: 16px;
  align-items: end;
}

.photo-river .media-frame:first-child {
  aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
}

.photo-river .media-frame:nth-child(2),
.photo-river .media-frame:nth-child(3) {
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
}

.day-section {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 320px 1fr;
  gap: 54px;
}

.day-list {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  border-top: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  border-left: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
}

.day-list div {
  min-height: 210px;
  padding: 26px;
  border-right: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  background: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.5);
}

.day-list span {
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 26px;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: var(--fs-xs);
  color: var(--soil);
}

.day-list h3 {
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  font-size: var(--fs-lg);
  color: var(--forest);
}

.day-list p {
  margin: 0;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
}

.invitation-panel {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) auto;
  gap: 40px;
  align-items: end;
  padding: 44px;
  background:
    linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(47, 111, 115, 0.12), rgba(211, 155, 49, 0.14)),
    rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.78);
  border: 1px solid var(--line);
}

.invitation-panel p {
  max-width: 720px;
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .home {
    gap: 64px;
  }

  .hero-content h1 {
    font-size: var(--fs-2xl);
  }

  .hero-content p:not(.eyebrow),
  .lede {
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
  }

  .letter-intro,
  .identity-grid,
  .plainly-inner,
  .day-section,
  .invitation-panel {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .arrival-notes {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }

  .photo-river {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .photo-river .media-frame,
  .photo-river .media-frame:first-child,
  .photo-river .media-frame:nth-child(2),
  .photo-river .media-frame:nth-child(3) {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 620px) {
  .home-hero {
    min-height: 68svh;
  }

  .hero-content {
    width: min(100% - 28px, 1180px);
    padding: 72px 0 74px;
  }

  .hero-coordinates {
    left: 14px;
    right: auto;
    bottom: 18px;
  }

  .arrival-notes,
  .portrait-stack,
  .day-list {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .portrait-stack .low {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .identity-copy h2,
  .plainly h2,
  .day-heading h2,
  .invitation-panel h2 {
    font-size: var(--fs-xl);
  }

  .invitation-panel {
    padding: 28px;
  }
}
</style>
